  "text": "The strongest evidence of biliary salt-induced AKI is the histological finding of bile cast nephropathy, but this can merely reflect reduced glomerular filtration rate (GFR), through a reduction in the washout of the casts, as stated by Heyman et al in a commentary of van Slambrouck's paper. In the same letter the authors cited the potent endogenous antioxidant role of bilirubin in experimental settings [CITATION_1] . Rats subjected to BDL with the development of biliary cirrhosis were more resistant to contrast nephropathy and their medullary thick limbs hardly developed hypoxic injury [CITATION_2] .",
